---
there must always be an opposite to good. It has no place in heaven, so of
necessity it haunts the mortal nature of this earthly sphere. Therefore, we
ought to escape from earth to heaven as quickly as we can; and the way to
escape is to become like God, as far as possible; and the way to become
like Him is to become holy, good and wise.
